Greek Financing Solutions Shouldn’t Be ‘Disruptive,’ IMF Says

-- B y   S a n d r i n e   R a s t e l l o
-- 
2011-06-09T14:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/portugal-facing-difficult-situation-imf-s-atkinson-says.html
The solutions chosen to fill  Greece ’s
financing gap “should not be disruptive” for financial
stability, a spokeswoman for the  International Monetary Fund 
said.  “Any involuntary debt restructuring or credit event”
would be “undesirable,” spokeswoman  Caroline Atkinson  told
reporters in  Washington  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
